Q. database migration in laravell
A. Migrations = PHP files that define database structure
	They allow you to create, modify, and share database schema in a structured way.
	
	Why use Migrations : 
	No need to manually write SQL every time
	Easy to manage schema changes
	Version control for DB
	Team collaboration becomes simple
	
	Create Migration  : php artisan make:migration create_users_table
	Migration File Structure  : 
		up() → Run migration (create/modify table)
		down() → Rollback (undo changes)
	Run Migration : php artisan migrate
	Rollback Migration	: php artisan migrate:rollback
	
